266
00:15:01.767 --> 00:15:04.300
"You are coming to dinner tonight, right?"

267
00:15:04.300 --> 00:15:08.213
"Chief, it is Hanwoo."
That is how they reel me in.

268
00:15:08.213 --> 00:15:10.300
Hanwoo is their bait.

269
00:15:10.300 --> 00:15:12.375
Honestly.

270
00:15:12.375 --> 00:15:14.877
Those kids do not have money either.

271
00:15:16.447 --> 00:15:18.413
I feel bad.

272
00:15:18.413 --> 00:15:22.151
Because of me, you missed dinner
even on your last day.

273
00:15:24.788 --> 00:15:27.223
Do not talk nonsense.

274
00:15:28.158 --> 00:15:31.927
Young people hate dinners with old guys.

275
00:15:36.601 --> 00:15:38.567
Earlier today,

276
00:15:40.370 --> 00:15:43.772
I nodded off for a bit,

277
00:15:45.408 --> 00:15:48.033
and a bright blue sea

278
00:15:48.033 --> 00:15:50.846
was right in front of me.

279
00:15:52.849 --> 00:15:55.151
A white yacht

280
00:15:55.834 --> 00:15:59.255
sliced through the waves,

281
00:15:59.676 --> 00:16:01.801
and I was at the bow,

282
00:16:01.801 --> 00:16:05.127
standing there in the wind.

283
00:16:10.133 --> 00:16:12.301
That sounds like an amazing dream.

284
00:16:13.861 --> 00:16:15.200
Amazing?

285
00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:16.439
No. It was a nightmare.

286
00:16:16.439 --> 00:16:18.774
I could never do that.

287
00:16:27.550 --> 00:16:29.501
By the way,

288
00:16:29.501 --> 00:16:31.653
did Jun Kyung call?

289
00:16:32.488 --> 00:16:36.492
She did.
She must be busy, but she still remembered.

290
00:16:37.282 --> 00:16:39.361
Call, my foot.

291
00:16:41.098 --> 00:16:43.332
Do you think I do not know her?

292
00:16:46.334 --> 00:16:48.077
Open wide!

293
00:16:48.077 --> 00:16:51.133
It is going in. It is going in!

294
00:16:51.133 --> 00:16:54.443
Don't throw that. No!

295
00:16:54.443 --> 00:16:56.713
Are you not eating?

296
00:16:56.713 --> 00:16:58.543
Hey, where are you going?

297
00:16:58.543 --> 00:17:00.950
- Come here. I am dying.
- Open wide.

298
00:17:00.950 --> 00:17:03.685
Good. You are eating well.

299
00:17:03.685 --> 00:17:05.367
Come here.

300
00:17:05.367 --> 00:17:09.525
Go catch her!

301
00:17:19.602 --> 00:17:23.072
Why do you always sulk alone, huh?

302
00:17:23.072 --> 00:17:25.208
Your bones will rot. Cover this up.

303
00:17:25.208 --> 00:17:27.509
Another tiring day.

304
00:17:27.509 --> 00:17:30.813
It starts with caffeine, and ends with alcohol.

305
00:17:32.115 --> 00:17:34.483
This is my favorite time.

306
00:17:35.385 --> 00:17:37.601
When the day is finally done,

307
00:17:37.601 --> 00:17:41.424
while Hyeong Jun puts the kids to bed
and sets out the drinks,

308
00:17:41.424 --> 00:17:44.026
I get a little moment

309
00:17:44.026 --> 00:17:46.901
alone, quiet, and kind of lonely,

310
00:17:46.901 --> 00:17:49.565
and it makes my heart race.

311
00:17:50.875 --> 00:17:53.595
Isn't that ridiculous?

312
00:17:53.595 --> 00:17:56.004
I got married so I would not be lonely.

313
00:17:57.241 --> 00:17:59.141
Does Hyeong Jun like it too?

314
00:17:59.810 --> 00:18:01.955
He cannot say a word.

315
00:18:01.955 --> 00:18:04.680
Who told him to have three kids?

316
00:18:06.467 --> 00:18:08.615
He likes it, he really does.

317
00:18:08.615 --> 00:18:10.819
He says he is made for it.

318
00:18:11.854 --> 00:18:14.047
His mom nags me

319
00:18:14.047 --> 00:18:17.515
for making her doctor son cook.

320
00:18:17.515 --> 00:18:19.648
I am my parents' precious daughter too.

321
00:18:23.967 --> 00:18:25.969
Finally, they're asleep.

322
00:18:25.969 --> 00:18:27.667
What are you having today?

323
00:18:27.667 --> 00:18:29.772
Well...

324
00:18:30.473 --> 00:18:32.542
Let us do bokbunja.

325
00:18:32.542 --> 00:18:35.043
Snack is up to the chef.

326
00:18:35.043 --> 00:18:37.246
Bokbunja, and I pick the snack.

327
00:18:37.246 --> 00:18:39.381
Give me a second.

328
00:18:42.652 --> 00:18:44.863
- He looks good.
- Of course.

329
00:18:44.863 --> 00:18:47.957
You know how much I love him.

330
00:18:48.602 --> 00:18:50.294
Love?

331
00:18:50.294 --> 00:18:51.929
What's wrong?

332
00:18:51.929 --> 00:18:54.029
Is it too cheesy?

333
00:18:54.543 --> 00:18:57.420
Everyone is so lovesick

334
00:18:57.420 --> 00:19:01.739
that they even eye other people's partners.

335
00:19:01.739 --> 00:19:05.683
How can you be this cold-blooded?

336
00:19:05.683 --> 00:19:08.244
- You're heavy.
- Come on.

337
00:19:08.244 --> 00:19:13.282
Love is supposed to be intense
and a little cringey.

338
00:19:13.884 --> 00:19:16.085
- Nice, right?
- No.

339
00:19:16.085 --> 00:19:18.353
Love is nice.

340
00:19:25.534 --> 00:19:27.167
Enjoy your meal.

341
00:19:27.167 --> 00:19:29.365
Thank you.

342
00:19:39.842 --> 00:19:44.447
[Matna Pork Cutlet]

343
00:19:44.447 --> 00:19:45.981
Welcome.

344
00:19:47.316 --> 00:19:49.645
Isn't the pork cutlet kind of dry?

345
00:19:49.645 --> 00:19:51.026
One order of spicy chewy noodles please.

346
00:19:51.026 --> 00:19:52.221
Go eat that at your place.

347
00:19:52.221 --> 00:19:53.790
Do you know what time it is?

348
00:19:53.790 --> 00:19:55.366
They probably already ate and cleaned up.

349
00:19:55.366 --> 00:19:57.026
Start coming home earlier.

350
00:19:57.026 --> 00:19:58.428
You have nothing to do anyway.

351
00:19:58.428 --> 00:20:00.785
I do not want to go home early.

352
00:20:00.785 --> 00:20:02.126
I feel like I am walking
on eggshells for no reason.

353
00:20:02.126 --> 00:20:03.325
Going Dutch?

354
00:20:03.325 --> 00:20:05.601
Pick up the tab sometimes.

355
00:20:10.072 --> 00:20:11.446
I had a company dinner last week.

356
00:20:11.446 --> 00:20:13.475
I did not ask.

357
00:20:14.312 --> 00:20:16.979
We crushed tripe first,
then went to a club after.

358
00:20:16.979 --> 00:20:19.115
I do not care.

359
00:20:19.115 --> 00:20:21.252
Your girlfriend performed there.

360
00:20:21.252 --> 00:20:23.052
Did you see her performance?

361
00:20:23.052 --> 00:20:25.172
All the guys at work were completely smitten.

362
00:20:25.172 --> 00:20:28.291
She is sparkling like crazy.

363
00:20:28.291 --> 00:20:31.852
One of the junior marketers is
your girlfriend's middle school classmate.

364
00:20:31.852 --> 00:20:33.830
They were chatting back and forth all night.

365
00:20:33.830 --> 00:20:35.931
He said he was going to make a move.

366
00:20:36.465 --> 00:20:39.592
He will not put on anything
unless it is designer.

367
00:20:39.592 --> 00:20:42.304
He pretty much treats his job like a hobby.

368
00:20:43.472 --> 00:20:44.317
Hey.

369
00:20:44.317 --> 00:20:45.775
Look at this.

370
00:20:45.775 --> 00:20:47.438
See, proof of trust and loyalty.

371
00:20:47.438 --> 00:20:50.212
That's disgusting.

372
00:20:51.814 --> 00:20:55.250
And that is why you are still single.

373
00:20:56.719 --> 00:20:59.155
By the way, of all days,

374
00:20:59.155 --> 00:21:02.092
were you really not eating at home tonight?

375
00:21:02.092 --> 00:21:03.798
Tonight?

376
00:21:04.660 --> 00:21:06.374
Why?

377
00:21:07.230 --> 00:21:11.133
You did forget today was
Dad's last day at the office, right?

378
00:21:12.335 --> 00:21:13.629
Oh, right.

379
00:21:13.629 --> 00:21:16.628
If you live on your own,
you should stay on top of this stuff.

380
00:21:16.628 --> 00:21:19.342
I live with them,
so I will just see them when I get home.

381
00:21:19.342 --> 00:21:22.488
You are crashing there,
not actually living there.

382
00:21:22.488 --> 00:21:24.614
Call him, even if it is late.

383
00:21:24.614 --> 00:21:26.570
And just so you do not forget,

384
00:21:26.570 --> 00:21:29.018
Mom and Dad's anniversary is Sunday.

385
00:21:29.018 --> 00:21:31.701
Why is Dad dragging us to his anniversary?

386
00:21:31.701 --> 00:21:35.526
I told you.
He is wrapping it up with his retirement too.

387
00:21:35.526 --> 00:21:38.160
Sunday. Seriously, do not forget.

388
00:21:41.911 --> 00:21:43.100
Here.

389
00:21:43.100 --> 00:21:43.934
What is this?

390
00:21:43.934 --> 00:21:46.635
She likes mint chocolate, right?

391
00:21:46.635 --> 00:21:50.708
Tell your dad thanks for all he has done.

392
00:21:50.708 --> 00:21:53.351
And do not go saying I bought it, okay?

393
00:21:53.351 --> 00:21:54.432
- I am out.
- Thank you.

394
00:21:54.432 --> 00:21:56.445
- Bye.
- Bye.

395
00:21:59.683 --> 00:22:02.652
<i>Sorry I have not called, I have been swamped.</i>

396
00:22:02.652 --> 00:22:05.320
<i>You have worked hard, Dad.</i>

397
00:22:29.367 --> 00:22:31.079
That scared me!

398
00:23:24.700 --> 00:23:26.387
Hey.

399
00:23:27.338 --> 00:23:29.501
Want to pack lunch

400
00:23:29.501 --> 00:23:31.292
and go to the park tomorrow?

401
00:23:31.292 --> 00:23:33.009
No.

402
00:23:33.009 --> 00:23:36.432
Why not? The weather has been so nice
and warm during the day.

403
00:23:36.432 --> 00:23:38.968
Watching people out walking around

404
00:23:38.968 --> 00:23:42.618
just makes me feel lonely.

405
00:23:47.990 --> 00:23:49.767
I have got so much time now.

406
00:23:49.767 --> 00:23:52.361
And there are so many places
I want to go with you.

407
00:23:52.361 --> 00:23:56.331
So who told you to quit, then?

408
00:23:58.785 --> 00:24:01.203
I didn't want to waste my time.

409
00:24:08.677 --> 00:24:10.834
Do you not

410
00:24:10.834 --> 00:24:13.348
get tired of me?

411
00:24:16.200 --> 00:24:18.253
Goodness.

412
00:24:19.221 --> 00:24:21.390
How could I?

413
00:24:21.390 --> 00:24:24.159
You are adorable.

414
00:24:26.629 --> 00:24:28.937
You will go to the park
with me tomorrow, right?

415
00:24:28.937 --> 00:24:30.967
Next time.

416
00:24:30.967 --> 00:24:32.868
Yeah, next time.

417
00:24:40.209 --> 00:24:43.145
There is no second act, okay?

418
00:24:43.145 --> 00:24:45.481
Any guy who just wants to get you into bed

419
00:24:45.481 --> 00:24:47.943
will pull out all the stops.

420
00:24:47.943 --> 00:24:49.153
Now what about the ones

421
00:24:49.153 --> 00:24:51.803
who say they want to take it slow?

422
00:24:51.803 --> 00:24:52.822
What do you think?

423
00:24:52.822 --> 00:24:55.057
They will "get to know you" first,

424
00:24:55.057 --> 00:24:57.360
then try just as hard to sleep with you.

425
00:24:57.360 --> 00:24:59.829
Bottom line, men are all the same.
That is my point.

426
00:24:59.829 --> 00:25:02.143
So I'm saying I'm done dating.

427
00:25:02.143 --> 00:25:06.669
Why burn my feelings
on the same kind of guy again and again?

428
00:25:06.669 --> 00:25:09.304
Then why did you go on the blind date?

429
00:25:09.972 --> 00:25:11.941
Well...

430
00:25:11.941 --> 00:25:13.122
Because I have a job.

431
00:25:13.122 --> 00:25:15.211
- Oh, please.
- I can play along when I need to.

432
00:25:15.211 --> 00:25:16.178
Okay.

433
00:25:16.178 --> 00:25:18.514
Says the woman
who bought new clothes and shoes for it.

434
00:25:18.514 --> 00:25:21.260
She was hoping for something.

435
00:25:21.260 --> 00:25:22.952
Hey, that was...

436
00:25:22.952 --> 00:25:23.953
Just being decent.

437
00:25:23.953 --> 00:25:25.187
- Basic manners.
- Oh my.

438
00:25:25.187 --> 00:25:29.994
And if no one can even do that,
being alone is easier.

439
00:25:29.994 --> 00:25:32.034
Right, Jun Kyung.

440
00:25:32.034 --> 00:25:36.031
One is the perfect number.

441
00:25:36.031 --> 00:25:37.233
- Stable.
- Yes.

442
00:25:37.233 --> 00:25:39.602
No surprises.

443
00:25:39.602 --> 00:25:41.837
Totally predictable,
or you do not even have to predict anything.

444
00:25:41.837 --> 00:25:43.372
- But...
- Exactly.

445
00:25:43.372 --> 00:25:45.514
It gets boring.

446
00:25:45.514 --> 00:25:47.315
Add one more and it becomes two,

447
00:25:47.315 --> 00:25:49.275
and suddenly it is messy and complicated.

448
00:25:49.275 --> 00:25:51.013
But it is also fun.

449
00:25:51.013 --> 00:25:52.155
Think about it.

450
00:25:52.155 --> 00:25:54.350
You cannot do anything by yourself.

451
00:25:54.350 --> 00:25:57.787
Look, if there are two of you,
at least you've got someone to nod along.

452
00:25:57.787 --> 00:25:58.627
Cheers!

453
00:25:58.627 --> 00:25:59.955
See? You can toast.

454
00:25:59.955 --> 00:26:02.024
You can hype each other up
and say you did great.

455
00:26:02.024 --> 00:26:03.959
You can say it is okay
and be there for each other.

456
00:26:03.959 --> 00:26:05.048
You can fight too.

457
00:26:05.048 --> 00:26:06.668
Right, you can fight.

458
00:26:06.668 --> 00:26:08.998
And then you can make up.

459
00:26:08.998 --> 00:26:11.348
Now add one more and it becomes three,

460
00:26:11.348 --> 00:26:14.904
and someone can pick a side or break it up.

461
00:26:14.904 --> 00:26:16.939
Is that not kind of fun?

462
00:26:16.939 --> 00:26:18.976
Still, not five.

463
00:26:18.976 --> 00:26:20.661
Huh?

464
00:26:22.378 --> 00:26:24.513
Sounds like you need six.

465
00:26:24.513 --> 00:26:25.848
No, no, lucky seven.

466
00:26:25.848 --> 00:26:28.050
Honey, we had bokbunja tonight,

467
00:26:28.050 --> 00:26:30.319
so should we make twins? Come here.

468
00:26:30.319 --> 00:26:31.958
Touch me and you are dead.

469
00:26:31.958 --> 00:26:33.189
Seven? Are you out of your mind?

470
00:26:33.189 --> 00:26:34.457
What are we, Snow White?

471
00:26:34.457 --> 00:26:35.869
Look, Jun Kyung.

472
00:26:35.869 --> 00:26:38.689
Happiness is not as close as you think.

473
00:26:38.689 --> 00:26:40.396
It is way out there, yeah?

474
00:26:40.396 --> 00:26:42.029
So we have to work for it.

475
00:26:42.029 --> 00:26:46.701
Trying to be happy is already
kind of sad, is it not?

476
00:26:54.620 --> 00:26:57.178
<i>Does working at it</i>

477
00:26:58.334 --> 00:27:00.549
<i>actually make you happy?</i>

478
00:27:11.327 --> 00:27:13.180
You are home?

479
00:27:13.180 --> 00:27:14.360
Yeah, I am here.

480
00:27:14.360 --> 00:27:15.366
You've eaten yet?

481
00:27:15.366 --> 00:27:16.433
Yeah, I already ate.

482
00:27:16.433 --> 00:27:17.234
How is Mom?

483
00:27:17.234 --> 00:27:18.480
She is asleep.

484
00:27:18.480 --> 00:27:20.234
Maybe the new pain meds did it.

485
00:27:20.234 --> 00:27:21.868
She has been exhausted lately.

486
00:27:21.868 --> 00:27:23.572
I see...

487
00:27:25.383 --> 00:27:27.467
Well...

488
00:27:27.467 --> 00:27:29.812
This is for your retirement.

489
00:27:29.812 --> 00:27:30.939
Congrats?

490
00:27:30.939 --> 00:27:33.183
Should I say congratulations?

491
00:27:33.183 --> 00:27:36.117
Anyway, thanks for all your hard work.

492
00:27:36.703 --> 00:27:37.934
You knew about it?

493
00:27:37.934 --> 00:27:39.520
Huh?

494
00:27:41.892 --> 00:27:43.224
I honestly forgot.

495
00:27:43.224 --> 00:27:44.843
I am sorry.

496
00:27:44.843 --> 00:27:46.262
Hye On bought this too.

497
00:27:46.262 --> 00:27:47.929
Hye On did?

498
00:27:48.597 --> 00:27:51.533
That is so sweet. Good kid.

499
00:27:53.335 --> 00:27:55.704
Your mom will really love this, right?

500
00:27:55.704 --> 00:27:58.107
Freeze it, and we will eat it on Sunday.

501
00:27:58.107 --> 00:28:00.244
Yeah, let's do that.

502
00:28:00.244 --> 00:28:03.078
- I am going to bed.
- Yeah, go on in.

503
00:28:32.767 --> 00:28:35.000
Out of all our classmates,

504
00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:37.581
I thought you'd marry first.

505
00:28:37.581 --> 00:28:39.887
Based on what?

506
00:28:39.887 --> 00:28:41.327
You don't remember?

507
00:28:41.327 --> 00:28:43.718
Senior Kyung Min.

508
00:28:44.620 --> 00:28:46.689
That stuffy, zero charm nerd.

509
00:28:46.689 --> 00:28:50.668
You chased him like he was the one.

510
00:28:50.668 --> 00:28:52.895
You even confessed to him.

511
00:28:52.895 --> 00:28:54.963
He turned me down.

512
00:28:55.648 --> 00:28:58.334
You confessed, got rejected,

513
00:28:58.334 --> 00:29:01.370
then fell for someone else right away.

514
00:29:01.370 --> 00:29:04.634
I miss the bold, fearless you

515
00:29:04.634 --> 00:29:06.043
from back then.

516
00:29:06.043 --> 00:29:08.368
We were young.

517
00:29:08.368 --> 00:29:09.245
Darn it.

518
00:29:09.245 --> 00:29:11.115
I'm telling you, stay the night.

519
00:29:11.115 --> 00:29:14.316
Your place is way too crowded.

520
00:29:15.219 --> 00:29:16.808
Hey.

521
00:29:16.808 --> 00:29:18.854
What can you even do alone?

522
00:29:18.854 --> 00:29:21.289
Besides being lonely?

523
00:29:22.059 --> 00:29:25.094
I'm not lonely, though.

524
00:29:25.094 --> 00:29:27.997
Never.

525
00:29:27.997 --> 00:29:29.965
Bye.

526
00:29:57.570 --> 00:30:03.100
<i>­</i>

527
00:30:03.100 --> 00:30:07.570
<i>­</i>

528
00:30:07.570 --> 00:30:15.070
<i>­</i>

529
00:30:16.440 --> 00:30:21.540
<i>­</i>

530
00:30:21.540 --> 00:30:26.470
<i>­</i>

531
00:30:26.470 --> 00:30:35.090
<i>­</i>

532
00:30:35.090 --> 00:30:39.460
<i>­</i>

533
00:30:39.460 --> 00:30:43.090
<i>­</i>

534
00:30:43.090 --> 00:30:47.820
<i>­</i>

535
00:30:47.820 --> 00:30:52.150
<i>­</i>

536
00:30:52.150 --> 00:30:58.370
<i>­</i>

537
00:30:58.370 --> 00:31:01.940
<i>­</i>

538
00:31:01.940 --> 00:31:06.650
<i>­</i>

