00:31:10.590 --> 00:31:17.170
<i>­</i>

541
00:31:17.170 --> 00:31:19.641
<i>Loneliness is my dirty little secret.</i>

542
00:31:20.200 --> 00:31:24.479
<i>No one can ever find out.</i>

543
00:31:25.381 --> 00:31:29.884
<i>If anyone starts to pry,</i>

544
00:31:31.039 --> 00:31:33.922
<i>my defenses snap on.</i>

545
00:31:35.234 --> 00:31:38.674
<i>Some people rush to explain it away.</i>

546
00:31:38.674 --> 00:31:41.296
<i>Some get angry.</i>

547
00:31:41.930 --> 00:31:44.732
<i>Some just run.</i>

548
00:31:46.701 --> 00:31:50.038
<i>People say you should own your loneliness,</i>

549
00:31:50.038 --> 00:31:52.841
<i>not hide it.</i>

550
00:31:52.841 --> 00:31:56.644
<i>But that feels as hard as death.</i>

551
00:31:57.467 --> 00:32:00.949
<i>So we dress up,</i>

552
00:32:00.949 --> 00:32:04.185
<i>do our makeup even louder,</i>

553
00:32:04.834 --> 00:32:09.591
<i>and meet people with smiles that fake warmth.</i>

554
00:32:10.744 --> 00:32:13.895
<i>So our weak spot stays hidden.</i>

555
00:32:15.297 --> 00:32:19.868
<i>It was a piece of every joy and sorrow.</i>

556
00:32:20.469 --> 00:32:23.750
<i>Want a song that fits this book?</i>

557
00:32:23.750 --> 00:32:26.370
<i>­</i>

558
00:32:26.370 --> 00:32:31.400
<i>­</i>

559
00:32:52.167 --> 00:32:54.335
That will be 9,000 won.

560
00:32:55.567 --> 00:32:57.272
What?

561
00:33:02.200 --> 00:33:04.012
What's going on?

562
00:33:09.318 --> 00:33:10.534
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

563
00:33:10.534 --> 00:33:12.420
Jeez!

564
00:33:45.172 --> 00:33:47.121
Why are you following me?

565
00:33:50.002 --> 00:33:53.094
I am headed the same way.

566
00:33:54.463 --> 00:33:55.897
Well...

567
00:33:56.434 --> 00:34:00.068
I should have hurried past you,

568
00:34:00.068 --> 00:34:03.625
or taken the long way around,

569
00:34:03.625 --> 00:34:06.174
but it is freezing today.

570
00:34:06.968 --> 00:34:09.310
I can still...

571
00:34:15.068 --> 00:34:16.951
It is fine.

572
00:34:23.792 --> 00:34:26.260
- This is not me tailing you, right?
- You startled me.

573
00:34:27.496 --> 00:34:28.764
This is not following you.

574
00:34:28.764 --> 00:34:30.832
We are just walking together, right?

575
00:34:34.136 --> 00:34:37.434
I am drinking this with my husband.

576
00:34:37.434 --> 00:34:39.340
Okay...

577
00:34:40.477 --> 00:34:42.443
Do you live here?

578
00:34:44.615 --> 00:34:46.614
Do you live here?

579
00:34:51.555 --> 00:34:53.921
I do not live here.

580
00:35:07.300 --> 00:35:10.505
What is with that bold psycho?

581
00:35:59.360 --> 00:36:05.710
<i>­</i>

582
00:36:05.710 --> 00:36:11.140
<i>­</i>

583
00:36:11.140 --> 00:36:17.840
<i>­</i>

584
00:36:17.840 --> 00:36:19.590
<i>­</i>

585
00:36:19.590 --> 00:36:22.210
He is entertaining on his own.

586
00:36:24.167 --> 00:36:26.547
How perfect.

587
00:36:44.057 --> 00:36:45.733
Excuse me.

588
00:36:46.635 --> 00:36:48.667
My wife is not feeling well,

589
00:36:48.667 --> 00:36:51.073
so overseas travel is hard.

590
00:36:51.073 --> 00:36:53.300
We want to travel within Korea,

591
00:36:53.300 --> 00:36:56.377
somewhere with minimal walking.

592
00:36:56.970 --> 00:36:58.913
Yes.

593
00:37:02.083 --> 00:37:05.100
If possible, with no walking at all.

594
00:37:05.100 --> 00:37:07.321
Well...

595
00:37:08.433 --> 00:37:12.327
We have a fully accessible option.

596
00:37:12.327 --> 00:37:15.713
How about a resort on Jeju Island?

597
00:37:15.713 --> 00:37:17.962
Oh, Jeju?

598
00:37:17.962 --> 00:37:22.069
You can use all our premium services.
How does that sound?

599
00:37:22.573 --> 00:37:24.334
It sounds great,

600
00:37:24.334 --> 00:37:25.974
but it will be expensive, right?

601
00:37:25.974 --> 00:37:28.776
An all-inclusive full package.

602
00:37:29.253 --> 00:37:31.545
What does inclusive mean?

603
00:37:34.482 --> 00:37:36.884
It means...

604
00:37:37.485 --> 00:37:38.787
everything is included.

605
00:37:38.787 --> 00:37:40.609
We do not need

606
00:37:40.609 --> 00:37:42.090
the full package.

607
00:37:42.090 --> 00:37:45.059
The basic plan is enough for us.

608
00:37:45.560 --> 00:37:49.897
The nice part is that we have many options.

609
00:37:50.406 --> 00:37:52.934
Special Gold, Fantastic Silver,

610
00:37:52.934 --> 00:37:55.469
then Beautiful Bronze.

611
00:37:57.539 --> 00:37:59.994
[Jeju Golden Tour, 4 nights, 5 days]

612
00:38:02.121 --> 00:38:05.280
Do you have anything cheaper, maybe?

613
00:38:05.280 --> 00:38:07.634
Like a normal Copper plan,

614
00:38:07.634 --> 00:38:10.451
or a simple Rusty Silver plan.

615
00:38:14.890 --> 00:38:18.659
Take a look.
This is the off-season special price.

616
00:38:19.261 --> 00:38:23.131
If we remove a few perks,
you can get up to 20 percent off.

617
00:38:23.131 --> 00:38:25.500
But then it is nonrefundable.

618
00:38:25.500 --> 00:38:27.169
Once we book, we will not cancel.

619
00:38:27.169 --> 00:38:29.171
We are definitely going.

620
00:38:29.171 --> 00:38:31.529
This plan fits you perfectly.

621
00:38:31.529 --> 00:38:34.275
Look at this.

622
00:38:34.809 --> 00:38:37.112
- Is the yacht included, too?
- Of course.

623
00:38:37.112 --> 00:38:41.822
You can choose a private yacht tour for two.

624
00:38:53.061 --> 00:38:55.630
How much is that one?

625
00:38:56.798 --> 00:38:58.400
That is 260,000 won.

626
00:38:58.400 --> 00:39:00.234
Would you like those flowers?

627
00:39:00.715 --> 00:39:02.434
No. For now, hold that one.

628
00:39:02.434 --> 00:39:04.405
Well...

629
00:39:05.040 --> 00:39:06.945
How much is that one?

630
00:39:06.945 --> 00:39:10.611
That one is 180,000 won.

631
00:39:11.913 --> 00:39:13.316
Well...

632
00:39:14.968 --> 00:39:18.052
Then...

633
00:39:18.834 --> 00:39:20.955
How much is this one?

634
00:39:21.823 --> 00:39:24.659
What do you need it for?

635
00:39:26.126 --> 00:39:28.763
I want to celebrate.

636
00:39:44.360 --> 00:39:47.630
<i>­</i>

637
00:39:47.630 --> 00:39:51.450
<i>­</i>

638
00:39:51.450 --> 00:39:58.240
<i>­</i>

639
00:39:58.240 --> 00:40:03.100
<i>­</i>

640
00:40:03.100 --> 00:40:05.880
<i>­</i>

641
00:40:05.880 --> 00:40:12.040
<i>­</i>

642
00:40:12.040 --> 00:40:15.680
<i>­</i>

643
00:40:15.680 --> 00:40:19.443
Was it 37 years?

644
00:40:19.443 --> 00:40:20.882
Huh?

645
00:40:20.882 --> 00:40:22.050
What?

646
00:40:22.050 --> 00:40:24.085
The anniversary starts from our photo day,

647
00:40:24.085 --> 00:40:26.743
the day we stamped it official.

648
00:40:26.743 --> 00:40:28.143
Let me see.

649
00:40:28.143 --> 00:40:30.267
It was after Jun Kyung turned one,

650
00:40:30.267 --> 00:40:34.827
so it is our 35th anniversary.

651
00:40:34.827 --> 00:40:37.947
Time feels like it flew by,

652
00:40:37.947 --> 00:40:40.801
and also like it crawled.

653
00:40:42.670 --> 00:40:44.271
Really?

654
00:40:45.073 --> 00:40:47.542
For me, it was only slow.

655
00:40:48.209 --> 00:40:50.378
What should you wear?

656
00:40:50.378 --> 00:40:52.567
Like Jun Kyung said,

657
00:40:52.567 --> 00:40:54.382
I should have gone to a nursing home.

658
00:40:54.382 --> 00:40:55.701
Come on.

659
00:40:55.701 --> 00:40:58.119
Why would you go when I am here?

660
00:41:00.424 --> 00:41:02.067
Honey,

661
00:41:02.067 --> 00:41:03.191
how about this?

662
00:41:03.191 --> 00:41:06.627
I liked how you looked in this.

663
00:41:07.669 --> 00:41:09.656
That outfit is too small on me.

664
00:41:24.212 --> 00:41:25.801
The thing is

665
00:41:25.801 --> 00:41:27.349
I knew it was broken,

666
00:41:27.349 --> 00:41:29.951
and I still left it alone.

667
00:41:29.951 --> 00:41:31.511
You should have called for service.

668
00:41:31.511 --> 00:41:34.871
You think you can get it fixed that day?

669
00:41:34.871 --> 00:41:37.791
The tech has a schedule,
and it has to match my day off.

670
00:41:37.791 --> 00:41:41.463
If it is hard to meet a repair tech,
how am I supposed to meet anyone?

671
00:41:41.463 --> 00:41:42.901
I get off work soon,

672
00:41:42.901 --> 00:41:44.152
want to come over to my place?

673
00:41:44.152 --> 00:41:45.467
I have something to do.

674
00:41:45.467 --> 00:41:47.270
What is it?

675
00:41:48.606 --> 00:41:51.105
Something really draining.

676
00:42:00.317 --> 00:42:02.115
<i>No.</i>

677
00:42:03.988 --> 00:42:06.387
<i>Honestly, something I am scared of.</i>

678
00:42:06.903 --> 00:42:09.457
If you missed my call,
you should've called me back.

679
00:42:09.457 --> 00:42:11.763
I told you I practiced till dawn, then slept.

680
00:42:11.763 --> 00:42:14.662
<i>You slept so long I got worried.</i>

681
00:42:14.662 --> 00:42:16.783
I was asleep, why worry?

682
00:42:16.783 --> 00:42:17.668
You are so pretty

683
00:42:17.668 --> 00:42:20.838
I worry guys will hit on you, even in my sleep.

684
00:42:20.838 --> 00:42:22.904
Oh, come on.

685
00:42:22.904 --> 00:42:24.743
Who are you meeting?

686
00:42:24.743 --> 00:42:26.264
You do not know them.

687
00:42:26.264 --> 00:42:28.179
Middle school friends.

688
00:42:28.179 --> 00:42:31.579
They are coming to see my show at the club,
so we will hang out after.

689
00:42:32.263 --> 00:42:33.982
Middle school friends?

690
00:42:33.982 --> 00:42:35.804
- Which ones?
- Oh, I am getting a call.

691
00:42:35.804 --> 00:42:37.683
- I'm gonna hang up.
- Okay, call me later.

692
00:42:37.683 --> 00:42:38.763
Make sure you call.

693
00:42:38.763 --> 00:42:40.255
I love you.

694
00:42:40.255 --> 00:42:41.942
Bye.

695
00:42:54.169 --> 00:42:55.816
What are you doing here?

696
00:42:57.230 --> 00:42:58.471
Nothing.

697
00:42:58.471 --> 00:43:01.175
You are not just dropping by
and leaving, right?

698
00:43:01.709 --> 00:43:03.677
Do not worry about it.

699
00:43:04.311 --> 00:43:05.771
Oh, come on.

700
00:43:05.771 --> 00:43:07.667
This is our parents' house.

701
00:43:16.691 --> 00:43:18.259
You did not seriously wait for me, did you?

702
00:43:18.259 --> 00:43:20.195
Are you crazy? Why would I wait for you?

703
00:43:20.195 --> 00:43:21.896
It is awkward if you come alone.

704
00:43:21.896 --> 00:43:24.201
A kid being awkward with their parents, really?

705
00:43:24.201 --> 00:43:26.298
Worry about yourself.

706
00:43:26.298 --> 00:43:27.235
I am fine.

707
00:43:27.235 --> 00:43:29.637
Yeah, sure you are.
You will be great at dating, though.

708
00:43:29.637 --> 00:43:32.574
It has been a while
since I asked you for money.

709
00:43:32.574 --> 00:43:34.159
Do I have to listen to that?

710
00:43:34.159 --> 00:43:35.143
Give me a break.

711
00:43:35.143 --> 00:43:37.815
Half your tuition comes out of my account.

712
00:43:37.815 --> 00:43:40.248
Astronomy for undergrad,
and your master's is...

713
00:43:40.248 --> 00:43:41.399
Culture something?

714
00:43:41.399 --> 00:43:43.199
It is cultural convergence.

715
00:43:43.199 --> 00:43:45.158
What about your PhD?

716
00:43:45.158 --> 00:43:45.959
Aerospace trade?

717
00:43:45.959 --> 00:43:47.759
I'm at the stage of choosing my path.

718
00:43:47.759 --> 00:43:49.399
You just keep changing yours.

719
00:43:49.399 --> 00:43:51.259
Can you ever stick with one thing?

720
00:43:51.259 --> 00:43:54.058
We finally meet and you have to talk like that.

721
00:43:54.058 --> 00:43:56.504
Was I wrong about anything?

722
00:43:56.504 --> 00:43:59.400
You think you are the best
in the universe, right?

723
00:43:59.400 --> 00:44:02.164
People do not go around
saying only nice things.

724
00:44:02.164 --> 00:44:04.405
Even if it is wrong.

725
00:44:04.405 --> 00:44:06.005
Sometimes you still have to say it.

726
00:44:06.005 --> 00:44:08.776
Sometimes it is good to hear it too, okay?

727
00:44:08.776 --> 00:44:11.184
On days like this, we should just eat out.

728
00:44:11.184 --> 00:44:13.344
You do not know Mom hates crowds?

729
00:44:13.344 --> 00:44:16.817
Don't set Mom off again.

730
00:44:27.467 --> 00:44:28.683
Okay, okay.

731
00:44:28.683 --> 00:44:31.098
All set.

732
00:44:31.799 --> 00:44:33.901
All good, one more time.

733
00:44:33.901 --> 00:44:35.334
All good.

734
00:44:35.334 --> 00:44:36.837
All good.

735
00:44:42.143 --> 00:44:44.311
Want me to put on your lipstick?

736
00:44:45.713 --> 00:44:48.248
My hands are fine.

737
00:45:06.067 --> 00:45:07.132
What do you think?

738
00:45:07.132 --> 00:45:09.370
It looks great on you, right?

739
00:45:10.672 --> 00:45:13.073
- Honey.
- Yeah?

740
00:45:14.645 --> 00:45:16.543
I am sorry.

741
00:45:17.311 --> 00:45:19.146
For what?

742
00:45:20.682 --> 00:45:22.416
For everything.

743
00:45:24.557 --> 00:45:26.821
You are getting better.

744
00:45:26.821 --> 00:45:29.490
Everything will be okay.

745
00:45:31.228 --> 00:45:32.534
By the way,

746
00:45:32.534 --> 00:45:35.663
is something burning?

747
00:45:35.663 --> 00:45:38.832
Oh no, the sauce.

748
00:45:48.009 --> 00:45:50.878
[Jeju travel voucher]

749
00:45:55.500 --> 00:45:56.968
That is all set.

750
00:45:56.968 --> 00:45:58.434
Dad, should I put this here?

751
00:45:58.434 --> 00:45:59.988
Yeah, sure.

752
00:45:59.988 --> 00:46:02.293
- And add the sliced potatoes too.
- Yeah.

753
00:46:02.293 --> 00:46:04.458
- Okay.
- And the meat too.

754
00:46:08.196 --> 00:46:10.998
Jun Seo, come here a second.

755
00:46:12.403 --> 00:46:14.035
Be careful.

756
00:46:14.035 --> 00:46:16.601
Ouch, it is hot.

757
00:46:16.601 --> 00:46:18.539
I told you to be careful.

758
00:46:20.241 --> 00:46:21.667
Okay.

759
00:46:21.667 --> 00:46:23.977
Yeah, bring the rest in.

760
00:46:25.780 --> 00:46:27.151
Dad, do you need help?

761
00:46:27.151 --> 00:46:28.850
No, I am all done.

762
00:46:28.850 --> 00:46:31.131
Just sit down.

763
00:46:43.633 --> 00:46:45.352
What's wrong?

764
00:46:47.602 --> 00:46:50.874
It is just kind of awkward.

765
00:46:50.874 --> 00:46:52.585
About what?

766
00:46:55.543 --> 00:46:57.034
My clothes?

767
00:46:57.034 --> 00:46:58.846
No.

768
00:47:14.632 --> 00:47:17.368
Mom, is there anything you need these days?

769
00:47:17.368 --> 00:47:19.270
Need what?

770
00:47:19.270 --> 00:47:21.235
Where would I even go?

771
00:47:26.910 --> 00:47:28.445
What about the hospital?

772
00:47:28.445 --> 00:47:30.077
Do you still go?

773
00:47:30.797 --> 00:47:32.946
How is your blood pressure lately?

774
00:47:36.553 --> 00:47:38.567
My mother.

775
00:47:38.567 --> 00:47:40.054
Well, look at you.

776
00:47:40.054 --> 00:47:42.460
You are looking very sexy today.

777
00:47:42.460 --> 00:47:43.925
You definitely take after me.

778
00:47:43.925 --> 00:47:45.881
You really know how to talk.

779
00:47:45.881 --> 00:47:48.629
Is that why everyone loves me?

780
00:47:48.629 --> 00:47:51.733
Even my professor will not stop looking for me.

781
00:47:51.733 --> 00:47:54.401
It is driving me up the wall.

782
00:48:01.008 --> 00:48:03.677
How have you been?

783
00:48:04.815 --> 00:48:06.180
At the hospital?

784
00:48:06.180 --> 00:48:08.015
It's been good.

785
00:48:08.820 --> 00:48:13.121
When you are young, being a doctor
feels impressive.

786
00:48:13.121 --> 00:48:16.023
When you get older, it is harder
to meet someone on your level.

787
00:48:16.023 --> 00:48:17.758
Mom.

788
00:48:20.561 --> 00:48:23.764
It has been a while,
so let us keep it positive.

789
00:48:25.266 --> 00:48:26.403
Why?

790
00:48:26.403 --> 00:48:28.602
It's not like Mom said anything wrong.

791
00:48:30.040 --> 00:48:32.039
Mom, Dad,

792
00:48:32.039 --> 00:48:35.409
happy anniversary.

793
00:48:37.378 --> 00:48:39.399
Congratulations from me too.

794
00:48:40.181 --> 00:48:41.416
You didn't have to get me anything.

795
00:48:41.416 --> 00:48:43.651
Thank you so much.

796
00:48:43.651 --> 00:48:45.520
I'll hire a caregiver for you,

797
00:48:45.520 --> 00:48:49.123
so you can see friends and go hiking.

798
00:48:49.123 --> 00:48:52.626
You have been running yourself ragged.
You never even get a break.

799
00:48:54.429 --> 00:48:56.758
How is Dad supposed to do that?

800
00:48:56.758 --> 00:48:59.067
Mom is by herself every day.

801
00:48:59.067 --> 00:49:00.401
Come on.

802
00:49:00.401 --> 00:49:03.404
She sat here alone till I got back.

803
00:49:03.404 --> 00:49:05.318
It wore her down the most.

804
00:49:05.318 --> 00:49:08.709
Now she does not have to, how great is that.

805
00:49:09.880 --> 00:49:11.646
Honey, does this ring a bell?

806
00:49:11.646 --> 00:49:13.816
The day of our first anniversary.

807
00:49:13.816 --> 00:49:16.384
We worked up the nerve
and went to a classic old-school restaurant.

808
00:49:16.384 --> 00:49:20.026
We ordered a hamburger steak
and tried wine for the first time.

809
00:49:20.026 --> 00:49:24.391
And we cracked up
because the wine stained our lips dark.

810
00:49:24.892 --> 00:49:27.464
Honey, you remember that, right?

811
00:49:27.464 --> 00:49:29.196
No, I do not.

812
00:49:30.531 --> 00:49:33.701
Sure, that was ages ago.

813
00:49:33.701 --> 00:49:35.068
It is ancient history.

814
00:49:35.068 --> 00:49:39.139
It has been over thirty years,
so of course you forgot.

815
00:49:45.934 --> 00:49:47.848
Honey, how about a toast?

816
00:49:49.022 --> 00:49:52.452
I already took my pain meds twice today.

817
00:49:53.402 --> 00:49:55.389
Oh, right.

818
00:49:56.190 --> 00:49:58.960
You shouldn't drink it. Sorry.

819
00:49:58.960 --> 00:50:01.128
You go ahead.

820
00:50:01.622 --> 00:50:04.131
No, I am not really craving it either.

821
00:50:05.700 --> 00:50:08.569
Honestly, plain water tastes best.

822
00:50:08.569 --> 00:50:10.704
I will have some.

823
00:50:14.678 --> 00:50:16.476
Want some too?

824
00:50:27.294 --> 00:50:30.357
I should have died then.

825
00:50:31.158 --> 00:50:33.067
If I had,

826
00:50:33.067 --> 00:50:36.197
you would not be stuck with water like this.

827
00:50:36.197 --> 00:50:39.366
You would be drinking wine
to your heart's content.

828
00:50:44.639 --> 00:50:48.475
Do you always have to bring up dying?

829
00:50:54.148 --> 00:50:57.384
I feel like I age ten years
whenever I visit this house.

830
00:50:58.649 --> 00:51:00.441
Why blame the house?

831
00:51:00.441 --> 00:51:02.356
Blame me.

832
00:51:02.356 --> 00:51:05.227
Just say I age you the moment you meet me.

833
00:51:05.227 --> 00:51:06.193
Mom.

834
00:51:06.193 --> 00:51:07.889
Moods spread, you know.

835
00:51:07.889 --> 00:51:09.796
Hey, Jun Kyung.

836
00:51:10.267 --> 00:51:11.832
Okay.

837
00:51:13.267 --> 00:51:14.150
Enough, everyone.

838
00:51:14.150 --> 00:51:17.125
How about we all do a toast together?

839
00:51:17.125 --> 00:51:18.730
It is a happy day.

840
00:51:18.730 --> 00:51:20.267
Why can't you just have a glass of wine

841
00:51:20.267 --> 00:51:23.176
on a day like this?

842
00:51:27.251 --> 00:51:30.685
That is not a consideration.

843
00:51:30.685 --> 00:51:32.923
That is you hurting me.

844
00:51:38.359 --> 00:51:39.592
- Drink it.
- Mom.

845
00:51:39.592 --> 00:51:42.096
It is fine.

846
00:51:43.197 --> 00:51:45.165
I can just drink it.

847
00:51:47.301 --> 00:51:48.772
Finish it, all of it.

848
00:51:48.772 --> 00:51:50.741
Mom.

849
00:51:50.741 --> 00:51:52.501
That's enough.

850
00:51:52.501 --> 00:51:54.208
I'll finish it.

851
00:52:04.852 --> 00:52:06.520
All right, time to blow out the candles.

852
00:52:06.520 --> 00:52:08.022
Wait a second.

853
00:52:08.022 --> 00:52:10.490
- Wait a second.
- Okay.

854
00:52:33.622 --> 00:52:36.049
Mom, are you aware
that outfit is squeezing you?

855
00:52:49.525 --> 00:52:52.433
- Honey.
- Yeah?

856
00:52:52.433 --> 00:52:55.069
I feel lightheaded.

857
00:52:55.069 --> 00:52:56.462
I need to lie down.

858
00:52:56.462 --> 00:52:58.258
Yeah, okay.

859
00:52:58.939 --> 00:52:59.763
Dad, I will handle it.

860
00:52:59.763 --> 00:53:02.376
No, sit down. I will do it, stay seated.

861
00:53:07.472 --> 00:53:09.164
Just sit down.

862
00:53:18.893 --> 00:53:21.432
Do I only get to say what Mom wants to hear?

863
00:53:21.432 --> 00:53:23.831
It was just a terrible accident.

864
00:53:23.831 --> 00:53:26.432
And by sheer luck, she did not die.

865
00:53:26.432 --> 00:53:27.702
But because Mom will not even commit to rehab,

866
00:53:27.702 --> 00:53:29.732
how long do we all have
to stay miserable like this?

867
00:53:29.732 --> 00:53:31.893
Stop wrecking Mom's day.

868
00:53:31.893 --> 00:53:34.741
She wrecked mine too.

869
00:53:37.411 --> 00:53:39.146
Grow up already.

870
00:53:39.146 --> 00:53:41.281
Please.

871
00:53:59.033 --> 00:54:01.768
Yeah, four people is too much.

872
00:54:07.801 --> 00:54:09.409
Honey.

873
00:54:10.033 --> 00:54:12.679
Let it go, okay?

874
00:54:14.229 --> 00:54:18.218
Jun Kyung is right anyway.

875
00:54:20.839 --> 00:54:22.723
I think

876
00:54:22.723 --> 00:54:25.626
I need to lose some weight.

877
00:54:25.626 --> 00:54:28.528
The doctor told me I should.

878
00:54:29.828 --> 00:54:30.897
Yeah.

879
00:54:30.897 --> 00:54:32.399
Do not overdo it.

880
00:54:32.399 --> 00:54:36.206
Let's take it slow, and do it together.

881
00:54:39.543 --> 00:54:41.141
What's wrong?

882
00:54:44.545 --> 00:54:46.713
What can I do

883
00:54:47.384 --> 00:54:51.518
without you?

884
00:54:58.427 --> 00:55:00.494
How am I supposed

885
00:55:01.231 --> 00:55:03.697
to manage without you?

886
00:55:08.973 --> 00:55:11.241
I am heading out.

887
00:55:11.241 --> 00:55:13.039
Get some rest.

888
00:55:22.486 --> 00:55:24.651
You are leaving now?

889
00:55:24.651 --> 00:55:26.720
Yeah. There is nothing else to do.

890
00:55:28.225 --> 00:55:31.091
If you go like this, Mom will feel awful.

891
00:55:42.190 --> 00:55:44.037
Another time.

892
00:55:56.016 --> 00:55:57.251
Go on in.

893
00:55:57.251 --> 00:56:00.059
It's freezing. Hurry home.

894
00:56:00.724 --> 00:56:02.789
Off you go.

895
00:56:06.010 --> 00:56:07.827
Jun Kyung.

896
00:56:10.363 --> 00:56:14.447
Six months, and this is your first time back.

897
00:56:19.202 --> 00:56:23.676
If your mom and I get 20 more years,

898
00:56:24.605 --> 00:56:27.381
we will share a meal

899
00:56:27.381 --> 00:56:30.650
about 40 times.

900
00:56:34.150 --> 00:56:36.991
We just used one, so that leaves 39.

901
00:56:36.991 --> 00:56:38.778
You got it?

902
00:56:46.000 --> 00:56:47.993
Come by more.

903
00:56:47.993 --> 00:56:50.167
Eat with your mom more often.

904
00:56:50.167 --> 00:56:51.838
Got it?

905
00:56:55.083 --> 00:56:56.710
Okay.

906
00:56:57.323 --> 00:56:59.112
Go on, get going.

907
00:57:01.852 --> 00:57:03.133
I am off.

908
00:57:03.133 --> 00:57:04.951
Go.

909
00:57:36.580 --> 00:57:37.200
<i>­</i>

910
00:57:37.200 --> 00:57:40.190
<i>­</i>

911
00:57:57.385 --> 00:57:59.572
Sol, it's me.

912
00:58:00.752 --> 00:58:02.809
Hello?

913
00:58:03.944 --> 00:58:06.179
You are silent.

914
00:58:07.881 --> 00:58:10.617
You must have hit the call button by accident.

915
00:58:11.251 --> 00:58:12.265
Okay?

916
00:58:12.265 --> 00:58:15.688
<i>Hey, that is itchy. Knock it off.</i>

917
00:58:15.688 --> 00:58:16.546
<i>Is that your sweet spot?</i>

918
00:58:16.546 --> 00:58:18.285
<i>Stop already.</i>

919
00:58:18.285 --> 00:58:21.594
<i>Why are your hands so scratchy?</i>

920
00:58:21.594 --> 00:58:23.716
Sol.

921
00:58:23.716 --> 00:58:24.902
<i>- Hey.
- That really stings.</i>

922
00:58:24.902 --> 00:58:26.367
- Sol.
<i>- Come on.</i>

923
00:58:26.367 --> 00:58:28.735
What are you doing right now?

924
00:59:09.943 --> 00:59:12.546
[Jeju travel voucher]

925
00:59:22.656 --> 00:59:25.925
I am not sure

926
00:59:26.968 --> 00:59:30.063
how you will take this.

927
00:59:30.534 --> 00:59:32.767
Living

928
00:59:32.767 --> 00:59:35.102
with you

929
00:59:35.102 --> 00:59:38.367
was tough sometimes,

930
00:59:38.367 --> 00:59:43.385
but there were so many good days too.

931
00:59:43.385 --> 00:59:45.745
So from now on...

932
00:59:49.901 --> 00:59:51.718
Well...

933
00:59:58.325 --> 01:00:00.539
So from now on,

934
01:00:00.539 --> 01:00:02.601
let us spend

935
01:00:02.601 --> 01:00:05.519
what we have left feeling happy.

936
01:00:05.519 --> 01:00:06.704
Okay?

937
01:00:06.704 --> 01:00:08.138
I love you.

938
01:00:08.138 --> 01:00:10.003
Sleep tight.

939
01:00:13.100 --> 01:00:23.040
<i>Timing and Subtitles brought to you by
7️⃣ Ways to Heal Team @Viki</i>

940
01:00:27.591 --> 01:00:29.289
Honey.

941
01:00:30.367 --> 01:00:32.538
I will be right back.

942
01:00:33.994 --> 01:00:36.063
Jun Seo, call 119.

943
01:00:36.063 --> 01:00:39.403
Call 119 right now.

944
01:00:45.172 --> 01:00:46.667
Honey.

945
01:00:46.667 --> 01:00:48.675
Honey.

946
01:00:56.250 --> 01:00:58.151
<i>I really believed</i>

947
01:00:59.300 --> 01:01:02.155
<i>there would be a next time.</i>

948
01:01:04.992 --> 01:01:07.431
<i>A next time where I could hand Mom</i>

949
01:01:07.431 --> 01:01:09.868
<i>a huge bouquet without thinking twice.</i>

950
01:01:09.868 --> 01:01:13.400
Honey, please open your eyes.

951
01:01:13.400 --> 01:01:17.508
<i>A next time where we sit
side by side on the grass</i>

952
01:01:17.508 --> 01:01:20.506
<i>and split a packed lunch.</i>

953
01:01:25.245 --> 01:01:27.413
<i>A next time</i>

954
01:01:28.252 --> 01:01:31.818
<i>for small greetings like "Good night, Mom."</i>

955
01:01:36.323 --> 01:01:39.064
<i>I thought those simple next times</i>

956
01:01:40.667 --> 01:01:44.831
<i>would still be waiting for us.</i>

957
